==== Academic Reanalysis

Kirvin-Quamme et al.\ (2025) published a formal reanalysis in _Frontiers in Psychology_ @kirvinquamme2025effort. Key findings:
    - Positive correlation ($r_s=0.38$, $p=0.03$) between hard task completion rate and proportion of hard task choices—indicating an ability confound
    - The hard task was simply too difficult for many ME/CFS patients to complete, regardless of preference
    - Data support interpretation that patients were “unable” rather than “unwilling”

